@SHossain Given that the "ACTIVATION" date is correct and both of the "DEADLINE" dates have past, it shouldn't matter as long as the "DEADLINE" is *in the past*
if you set "DEADLINE" to yesterday it would still yield the same results as the rest of the network has already accepted it as having past and now a requirement
The only issue that could arise is if you set it in the future and tried to do sprout - in which case your node would believe it valid and the rest of the network would refuse it
